1.7 million fentanyl pills, other drugs seized in Operation Double Down
By KJZZ,
36 minutes agoA major drug network responsible for shuttling drugs from Mexico into Arizona for U.S. distribution was halted with Operation Double Down, according to officials. The seven-month led to the seizure of 1.7 million fentanyl pills, along with cocaine and other narcotics. An additional 28 firearms and $200,000 were seized. Phoenix...
